EDSFooter.usage:
```html
<eds-footer name="GE HealthCare. GE is trademark of General Electric Company use under trademark license."
  utility=[
    { name: 'Privacy', url: '#!' },
    { name: 'Terms', url: '#!' },
    { name: 'Accessibility', url: '#!' },
    { name: 'Cookies', url: '#!' }
  ]
  status=[
    { name: 'Status', content: 'Ready' },
    { name: 'Mode', content: 'Research' },
    { name: 'Version', content: '5.4' }
  ]
  navigation=[
    {
      name: 'Shop',
      url: '#!',
      children: [
        { name: 'Accessories & Supplies', url: '#!' }, { name: 'Clinical Consumables', url: '#!' }
      ]
    },
    {
      name: 'Support',
      url: '#!',
      children: [
        { name: 'Contact Us', url: '#!' }, { name: 'Community Forum', url: '#!' }
      ]
    },
    {
      name: 'Repair',
      url: '#!',
      children: [
        { name: 'Service Documents', url: '#!' }, { name: 'Repair Center Locator', url: '#!' }
      ]
    }
  ]>

</eds-footer>
```
The property `preventRedirection` allows to avoid redirection made by the component and require to manage navigation manually.

The following CSS variables are available for styling :

CSS Variable | Description
:----------------|:-------------
--eds-footer-background | Set the background color for the footer
--eds-footer-text-color |Set the color of the footer text
--eds-footer-link-color | Set the color of the footer links
--eds-footer-status-background-color | Set the background color of the status bar
--eds-footer-status-text-color | Set the text color within the status bar
--eds-footer-navigation-background | Set the background color for the navigation columns
